          B
          
            
              o
              l
              d
            
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle B_{\mathrm {old} }}
   and 
  
    
      
        
          B
          
            
              n
              e
              w
            
          
        
        ,
      
    
    {\displaystyle B_{\mathrm {new} },}
   respectively.
Proof: Using the above definition of the change-of basis matrix, one has

  
    
      
        
          
            
              
                z
              
              
                
                =
                
                  ∑
                  
                    j
                    =
                    1
                  
                  
                    n
                  
                
                
                  y
                  
                    j
                  
                
                
                  w
                  
                    j
                  
                
              
            
            
              
              
                
                =
                
                  ∑
                  
                    j
                    =
                    1
                  
                  
                    n
                  
                
                
                  (
                  
                    
                      y
                      
                        j
                      
                    
                    
                      ∑
                      
                        i
                        =
                        1
                      
                      
                        n
                      
                    
                    
                      a
                      
                        i
                        ,
                        j
                      
                    
                    
                      v
                      
                        i
                      
                    
                  
                  )
                
              
            
            
              
              
                
                =
                
                  ∑
                  
                    i
                    =
                    1
                  
                  
                    n
                  
                
                
                  (
                  
                    
                      ∑
                      
                        j
                        =
                        1
                      
                      
                        n
                      
                    
                    
                      a
                      
                        i
                        ,
                        j
                      
                    
                    
                      y
                      
                        j
                      
                    
                  
                  )
                
                
                  v
                  
                    i
                  
                
                .
              
            
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\begin{aligned}z&=\sum _{j=1}^{n}y_{j}w_{j}\\&=\sum _{j=1}^{n}\left(y_{j}\sum _{i=1}^{n}a_{i,j}v_{i}\right)\\&=\sum _{i=1}^{n}\left(\sum _{j=1}^{n}a_{i,j}y_{j}\right)v_{i}.\end{aligned}}}
  As 
  
    
      
        z
        =
        
          
            ∑
            
              i
              =
              1
            
            
              n
            
          
          
            x
            
              i
            
          
          
            v
            
              i
            
          
          ,
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle z=\textstyle \sum _{i=1}^{n}x_{i}v_{i},}
   the change-of-basis formula results from the uniqueness of the decomposition of a vector over a basis.

Example
