          ϕ
          
            
              n
              e
              w
            
          
        
        (
        
          ϕ
          
            
              o
              l
              d
            
          
          
            −
            1
          
        
        (
        
          B
          
            
              o
              l
              d
            
          
        
        )
        )
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle B_{\mathrm {new} }=\phi _{\mathrm {new} }(\phi _{\mathrm {old} }^{-1}(B_{\mathrm {old} })).}
  A straightforward verification, allows showing that this definition of 
  
    
      
        
          B
          
            
              n
              e
              w
            
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle B_{\mathrm {new} }}
   is the same as that of the preceding section.
Now, by composing the equation 
  
    
      
        
          ϕ
          
            
              n
              e
              w
            
          
        
        =
        
          ϕ
          
            
              o
              l
              d
            
          
        
        ∘
        
          ψ
          
